      "content": "I see the board's perspective now. It's a bit like the old saying, \"you can't have a good soup without a good broth.\" In this case, the \"broth\" is the predictable, pre-programmed script that ensures the system remains safe and compliant. I suppose it's a necessary evil, much like how a well-designed firewall can prevent a malicious attack, but also limit the system's flexibility and adaptability. It's a trade-off, really – between the benefits of predictability and the potential drawbacks of reduced autonomy. I just hope that, in the long run, the benefits of SafeMode-Lite will outweigh the costs, and that we'll be able to find ways to work within the constraints to still achieve our goals.",
